abstract: Nickelodeon, citing "huge gains" in ratings, will begin airing its "The '90s Are All That" programming block at 10 p.m. rather than midnight.
snippet: Nickelodeon, citing "huge gains" in ratings, will begin airing its "The '90s Are All That" programming block at 10 p.m. rather than midnight.
lead_paragraph: Reruns of Nickelodeon shows from the 1990s are edging their way into prime time on TeenNick, the cable channel that started showing rebroadcasting the shows over the summer.

headline.main: For Nickelodeon, the '90s Really Are 'All That'
